main event: A sighting of an unidentified object over Anaheim, California in March 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as silver, orange, green, and white in color., The observation lasted for 30 minutes., The observer mentioned the object appeared to be a satellite during the last few minutes of the sighting., The observer noted both night and daylight conditions during the sighting., A buzzing sound was reported associated with the object.
witness description: The witness reported seeing a flying saucer-like object.
